In this article, White House Press Secretary Jay Carney discusses the President's decision to delay votes in Congress in order to pursue a diplomatic solution for Syria. Carney emphasizes that the credible threat of US military force brought about this diplomatic opening and explains that the President believes it is the responsible thing to do to explore the potential for a diplomatic resolution. He also addresses questions about the timeline for progress on the diplomatic front and the possibility of US boots on the ground in Syria. Additionally, Carney discusses the President's upcoming meetings with the Brazilian Foreign Minister and the progress on the continuing resolution in Congress. He also addresses criticism of the President's speech and the zigzag nature of the administration's foreign policy. Finally, Carney emphasizes the importance of exploring the diplomatic avenue and reiterates the US's commitment to supporting the Syrian opposition.